===Etymology 1===
{{ja-kanjitab|かつら|yomi=k|alt=楓}}
From {{inh|ja|ojp|-|sort=かつら}}. Originally a compound of {{compound|ja|sort=かつら|香|tr1=ka|t1=fragrance, good smell|出|tr2=zu|t2=to come out, to put something out}} + {{m|ja|ら|tr=ra|pos=nominalizing suffix}}: "that which puts out a good smell", from the way the wood smells good.

====Pronunciation====
{{ja-pron|かつら|acc=0|acc_ref=DJR,NHK}}

====Noun====
{{ja-noun|かつら|カツラ}}

# [[katsura]] tree, {{taxfmt|Cercidiphyllum japonicum|species}}, also called the Japanese Judas tree
# {{lb|ja|Chinese mythology|sort=かつら}} a tree on the [[moon]], from a Chinese legend that the phases of the moon were caused by {{taxfmt|Lauraceae|family}} trees budding, blossoming, then dropping their flowers and leaves again as if in accelerated seasons
#: {{syn|ja|月桂|tr=gekkei}}
# [[julienne]]d [[raw]] [[daikon]], used as a [[garnish]] for [[sashimi]]
# {{syn of|ja|肉桂|tr=nikkei|t= cinnamon or cassia tree}} 
# {{q|by extension}} {{syn of|ja|桂皮|tr=keihi||cinnamon or cassia bark}}

